Stocks Extend Losses on Concern Over Europe Bank Capital to Weather Crisis

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-12-08T16:04:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/stocks-extend-losses-on-concern-over-europe-bank-capital-to-weather-crisis.html
U.S. stocks extended losses after the
European Banking Authority said the region’s banks will need to
raise 114.7 billion euros ($152.7 billion) in fresh capital to
weather the sovereign debt crisis.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index lost 1 percent to 1,248.59
at 11:03 a.m. in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
